dct_description_sm: Includes plan of temple ruins, illustration of stone relief work [scale ca. 1:7], and lithograph panorama of ruins, immediate surroundings, and Red Sea coast. Closets, holes in structure, staircases, and dimensions are shown in temple plan. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 6 (1836), pp. 96-100; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.47 1877
